Alcohol eNCA PORT ELIZABETH - The Eastern Cape government has met with the alcohol industry to discuss the worrying rise in COVID-19 cases in the province.
The delegation included Health Department heads and the police. READ: Premier wants alcohol banned in Eastern Cape Concerns raised include alcohol outlets not complying with liquor act regulations and lockdown Level 1 requirements. It is said this is causing an increase in COVID-19 infections and putting pressure on the health system. The alcohol industry has committed to training and deploying 80 community patrollers in hotspot areas in the province. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.